reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Amazing for the price, not my preferred quarter inch.
reviews.reviewText: Okay, they work fine, and the cost is great, but I don't like them personally.Overall, the chords are fine. They work, they haven't broken, and they are cheap. For a high school band that doesn't have any money, BUY THESE!! They do the work, there's NOTHING wrong with them, and it is one of the best deals for the money you're spending. However, there are some things to consider for those with the money to choose.1. They are cheap. It is a plastic casing around the jack, and they are thin and overall feel cheap.2. Because they are thin, they tangle easily. Just a pet peeve of mine, but a big enough one that I don't take these places or use them for guitar--> amp. For amp to amp or pedals to amp, it's fine, I route them, and they stay, but in any situation where they move, they're annoying.Again, they aren't bad! Especially for the price, but there are just a few things that would make me choose different cables instead.

reviews.reviewText: I am absolutely thrilled with the Elebase 1/4 Inch TRS Instrument Cable 20ft 2-Pack in the vibrant blue color! These cables have completely transformed my music setup. The 20-foot length gives me the freedom to move around comfortably during performances, without any worry about signal loss or interference.The straight 6.35mm male jack stereo audio connectors are incredibly sturdy and reliable, ensuring a secure connection every time. Whether I'm plugging in my guitar, keyboard, or any other instrument, the sound quality remains consistently crisp and clear, without any unwanted noise or distortion.The blue color adds a touch of style and uniqueness to my equipment, making it easy to identify my cables amidst a tangle of wires. The attention to detail in the design is evident, and it's clear that Elebase values both form and function.Furthermore, the 2-pack is a fantastic value for the price. Having an extra cable on hand is always handy, and I appreciate the thoughtfulness of including a backup. These cables have quickly become an integral part of my setup, and I can confidently say that they have exceeded my expectations in every aspect. If you're looking for reliable, high-quality instrument cables that not only deliver outstanding performance but also add a pop of color to your gear, the Elebase 1/4 Inch TRS Instrument Cable is an excellent choice!
